ActsLikeGit
===========

ALG automagically saves the history of a given text or string field.  It sits over the top of
an ActiveRecord model; after a value is committed to the database, the plugin writes the
new value to a text file and commits it to a git repository.  This way you get all the advantages
of using Git as version-control.

Usage:

    class Post < ActiveRecord::Base
      versioning(:title) do |version|
        version.repository = '/home/git/repositories/postal.git'
        version.message = lambda { |post| "Committed by #{post.author.name}" }
      end
    end

To view the complete list of changes:

  >> @post = Post.find 15
  <Post:15>
  >> @post.title
  => 'Freddy'
  >> @post.history(:title)
  => ['Joe', 'Frank', 'Freddy]
  >> @post.log
  => ['bfec2f69e270d2d02de4e8c7a4eb2bd0f132bdbb', '643deb45c12982dde75ba71657792a2dbdda83e6', '1ce6c7368219db7698f4acc3417e656510b4138d']
  >> @post.revert_to '1ce6c7368219db7698f4acc3417e656510b4138d'
  >> @post.title
  => 'Joe'



